{"ID":270247, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"247\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs246.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs248.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 247<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">wine,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and we shall finally have to come to the same conclusion that Paul did&mdash;&ldquo;No man knows\n  the things of God but by the Spirit of God;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> for with the great revelations of Paul when he was\n  caught up into the third heaven and saw things that were not lawful to utter,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> no man was apprised\n  of it until he mentioned it himself fourteen years after; and when John had the curtains of heaven\n  withdrawn,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and by vision looked through the dark vista of future ages, and contemplated events that\n  should transpire throughout every subsequent period of time, until the final winding up\n  scene<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span>&mdash;while he gazed upon the glories of the eternal world, saw an innumerable company of\n  angels<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> and heard the voice of God&mdash;it was in the Spirit, on the Lord&rsquo;s day,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> unnoticed and\n  unobserved by the world.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"wideEllipse\">* * *<\/p>\n\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Necessity of Prayer<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The Lord cannot always be known by the thunder of His voice,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> by the display of His glory or\n  by the manifestation of His power, and those that are the most anxious to see these things, are the\n  least prepared to meet them,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and were the Lord to manifest His powers as He did to the children of\n  Israel,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> such characters would be the first to say, &ldquo;Let not the Lord speak any more, lest we His\n  people die.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">We would say to the brethren, seek to know God in your closets,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> call upon him in the fields.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span>\n  Follow the directions of the Book of Mormon, and pray over, and for your families, your cattle, your\n  flocks, your herds, your corn, and all things that you possess; ask the blessing of God upon all your\n  labors, and everything that you engage in.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> Be virtuous and pure;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> be men of integrity and truth;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span>\n  keep the commandments of God;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and then you will be able more perfectly to understand the\n  difference between right and wrong&mdash;between the things of God and the things of men;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> and your\n  path will be like that of the just, which shineth brighter and brighter unto the perfect day.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The True Use of Tongues<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Be not so curious about tongues, do not speak in tongues except there be an interpreter\n  present;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> the ultimate design of tongues is to speak to foreigners,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and if persons are very anxious\n  to display their intelligence, let them speak to such in<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108926\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108926)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108926)\">Acts 2:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109440\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109440)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109440)\">1 Cor. 2:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109690\"><a